quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  21,42,"Say: who protects you in the night and the day from the beneficent? Yet they turn away from remembering their Master"
  21,43,Or do they have gods that guard/defend them against Us? They cannot help themselves and they are not accompanied (and helped) by Us
  21,44,"No, but We gave these and their fathers enjoyment until the life lengthened for them (and they had a long life). Do they not see that We come to the earth and reduce it from its sides? So are they the winners"
  21,45,"Say: I only warn you with the revelation. And the deaf do not hear the call when they are warned"
  21,46,"And if a single blow of your Master’s punishment touches them, they shall say: woe to us, indeed we were wrongdoers"
  21,47,"And We set up the scales of justice on the resurrection day, then no person is wronged a bit, and even if it is weights of a mustard seed We bring it (into account), and We are sufficient for accounting"
  21,48,And We have certainly given Moses and Aaron the criterion (of good and bad) and a light and a reminder for those who control themselves
  21,49,"those who fear their Master in secret, and they are in awe of the hour (of resurrection)"
  21,50,And this (Quran) is a blessed reminder that We sent it down. So do you deny it